This article is a press gaggle by Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton aboard Air Force One en route to Austin, Texas. Burton discusses various topics including the President's view on fundraising, the importance of education, the search for Christy Romer's replacement, the President's visit to Texas, the state of the Texas economy, the President's involvement in Democratic campaigns, the cement plug in the Gulf, seafood from the Gulf, the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, North Korea's actions, border security, and the President's criticism of George W. Bush.